original: Jennes, Karl Baltzar, kyrkoherde, Ringarum, f. 30/11/92 i Misterhult, Kalmar 1., av Efraim J. o. Charlotta Hasselgren. — Stud:ex. i Linköp. 12, teol. fil. ex. 14, teol. kand. o. prakt, teol. prov 17, prästv. f. Linköp. stift 18. V. pastor i V. Husby 18^ kommin. i Hässleby 21, kyrkoh. i Ringarum sed. 32. Ordf. i skolstyr., kyrkostämma, barnhemsstyr. o. hem-bygdsfören. Skr.: Den kristna lära (handledn. f. konfirm :und :visn.).
translated: Jennes, Karl Baltzar, clergyman, Ringarum, born on November 30, 1892 in Misterhult, Kalmar 1st district, son of Efraim J. and Charlotta Hasselgren. — Completed high school in Linköping in 1912, obtained a Bachelor's degree in theology in 1914, passed theological candidate exams and practical theological examinations in 1917, ordained as a priest in the Linköping Diocese in 1918. Assistant pastor in Västra Husby from 1918, curate in Hässleby from 1921, parish priest in Ringarum since 1932. Chairman of the school board, church assembly, orphanage board, and local historical society. Writings: The Christian Doctrine (guidebook for confirmation education).
